1 No. 2766 of the 1st Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the
2 sum of Nine Million Four Hundred Eighty Thousand Four Hundred
3 Twenty-one Dollars ($9,480,421.00) shall be used to meet the
4 obligations required in the consent decree pursuant to case number
5 23-cv-81-GKF-JFJ filed in the United States District Court for the
6 Northern District of Oklahoma.
7 SECTION 3. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
8 Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services in Enrolled House Bill
9 No. 2766 of the 1st Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the
10 sum of Eighteen Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars
11 ($18,500,000.00) shall be used for the continuum of care for
12 children in crisis.
13 SECTION 4. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
14 Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services in Enrolled House Bill
15 No. 2766 of the 1st Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the
16 sum of One Million Three Hundred Thousand Dollars ($1,300,000.00)
17 shall be used to maintain services for veterans and their families.
18 SECTION 5. The Commissioner of Mental Health and Substance
19 Abuse Services may request through the Director of the Office of
20 Management and Enterprise Services the early transfer by the
21 Oklahoma Tax Commission of tax collections to the General Revenue
22 Fund for the purpose of early allocation to the Department’s
23 disbursing funds to alleviate cash-flow problems.
24 SECTION 6. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
